title: For Sale:  SOLD!!! Mossberg .270 4x4 Synthetic, Like New. Selling to buy parts for my time machine.
location: Saint Paul, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
I bought a Mossberg 4x4 .270 last year and absolutely loved it, however the price to feed it makes it prohibitive for me to become as proficient as I would like with it. Do not get me wrong, it is a tack driver with a good scope, I just flinch like a sissy when the thing goes off. The recoil is a lot more than I expected. Compared to the .308 I own, this one is amazing where recoil is concerned. 

It has the lightning trigger, which in my opinion has no peer. It is adjustable, you can add more weight to the pull or lessen it. Right now, it's feather light and out of the box it was perfect for me. It is one of those rifles you'll enjoy shooting. I simply can't afford to take it to the range as much as I'd like.

I have put about 40 rounds through it, and have a box of Privi Partisan 150 grain to go with it. It is like new in box, as shown. I had a scope on it, but took it off as I think people have their own preferences as to what scopes they like, and the one I had was a cheap one anyway. 

I paid $400.00 plus tax for it. It's like new, in box with all the stickers and everything. It would be an excellent hunting rifle. Especially if you are hunting larger game, like dinosaurs, or hostile aliens from another planet. I figured if I got my time machine up and running, I would head back to the pleistocene era to take down a sabretooth tiger, or a direwolf. I could head back further to the Cretaceous period and maybe take down a Tyrannosaurus. I have always wondered what what a Triceratops would taste like. 

The upside to owning a time machine would be the hunting. I worry I may have already gone back, as it seems nobody knows how to use the words There, Their and They're. I need money to fund my time machine construction so I can not only go back in time and hunt, but to go back in time to undo what my future self may have done to screw up everyone's spelling. 

If I can stop Hillary Clinton from becoming president, I'll fix that too. Just saying. I can see a connection to stupid people who can't spell, and a Hillary Presidency. Tell me I'm wrong. Anyway, $300.00 will help me move forward with my time machine. In exchange, you get the rifle, ammunition, and the bragging rights to meeting a time traveler who is stranded here.

title: For Sale:  CZ52 7.62x25. Exc. shape and shooter. All #'s match.
postcontent:
Very nice CZ52.  Two mags and the cleaning rod included. Has original phosphate finish showing some handling marks, but still looks great. Internall in excellent condition. All the numbers match.  Has original plastic grips in very good condition with no cracks.  Gun has a decocker.  This thing sounds like a 357 when you fire it.  The rounds are going around 1600 fps muzzle velocity. It makes a great fireball too.

I researched all the markings and came up with the following: the phosphate instead of blued finish indicates it wasn't a refurbished pistol. The crossed swords and number 53 indicate it is Czech Army and made in 53, the "rid" also incidates it was army production, not civilian.  The circled T on the barrel inside the chamber indicates it passed military inspection for safety and the de-cocker passed.  The various other marks are for the workers who might have assembled it and the circled vot or vor is probably the plant that did any refinishing or work on it before it was sent back out into the world.

There are no import marks that I can find. They should be on the bottom of the frame between the trigger guard and the end of the barrel. Oh well, it is simply a very nice looking and shooting pistol.  Kinda looks like what the desert eagle might have been imagined to look like in the 50's for some sci-fi movie.

$300 and I'll throw in 100 rounds of ammo.
